ed electrons radiating\nfrom radio to VHE gamma-rays through synchrotron and inverse Compton processes.\nIn addition when correcting for the distance, all SNRs show a surprisingly\nsimilar gamma-ray luminosity supporting the idea of a common emission\nmechanism. While the gamma-ray emission is likely to be leptonic dominated,\nthis does not rule out efficient hadron acceleration in those SNRs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 Jun 2015 20:01:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-05"}
